Nicholson County is named in honour of the Statesman, Sir Charles Nicholson (1808-1903).

Nicholson County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It contains the towns of Hillston , Goolgowi , Gunbar , Merriwagga , Goorawin and Langtree . The Lachlan River is its north-western boundary.
